    {
      "id": "ef3c8714c3fd90ecbd242dbc5796ee1c4d96c495",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-10-17 03:54:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nHi Niu, do you have any more questions about this patch?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "ca637bdec23e767b61419109172b4a4e8f45f3f8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 104,
        "name": "Niu Yawei",
        "email": "yawei.niu@intel.com",
        "username": "niu",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-10-17 06:57:58.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nThe question now is how to avoid the contention on the global lock 'cl_envs_guard' (especially on fat core system). I personally don't think it's a good idea to add this back to resolve the problem under memory pressure.\n\nWhat about reserve some env and only use them under memory pressure (ll_releasepage(), ll_writepage())? so that we can avoid more memory allocation when try to reclaim memory under mem pressure.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "cf64b4395cea8a917e7ed21f0f4b850e2d1ba2c4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-10-17 07:11:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nWe can only see the contention on PPC nodes so far, so this is not a generic problem. I have already worked out another patch to use a percpu array to cache cl_envs.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "243ddc197bac05993e3134e1b5528c50e4dbed13",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-10-21 21:22:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nNiu, do you have more question about this patch?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "55272d1418ee2ae7c888a96e96ccab1a6e2985e3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 104,
        "name": "Niu Yawei",
        "email": "yawei.niu@intel.com",
        "username": "niu",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-10-22 02:23:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI think we'd update the commit comment with more detailed information, such as: why the patch kills performance (in which situation), and how the LU-2622 will be addressed in the  follow-on patch.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "4af5852e23ba302d6a0f696e0420b3a5e603df7e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 4,
        "name": "Jinshan Xiong",
        "email": "jinshan.xiong@intel.com",
        "username": "Jay",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-10-22 02:31:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nSure, I will describe how this patch will kill performance, but the solution is actually out of the scope of this patch.\n\nPlease review the following patches. We need to land the patch asap.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
